IAM Documentation Menu S3 &raquo;
Best practices:
Lock away your AWS Account Root Access Keys. Create individual IAM Users. Configure strong pasword policy for your users. Rotate credentials regularly. Remove unnecessary credentials. Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) for priviliged users. Use Groups to assign permissions to IAM Users. Use AWS Defined Policies to assign permissions whenever possible. Use Policy Conditions for Extra security. Grant least privilige. Use Access Levels to Review IAM Permissions.

